{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-11",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_11_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Fat Man",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 0.7,
  "page_end_sec": 241.68,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.574,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.7,
      "end": 3.66,
      "text": "Chapter 11 of The Maltese Falcon by Dashiell Hammett."
    },
    {
      "start": 4.5,
      "end": 6.92,
      "text": "This LibriVox recording is in the public domain."
    },
    {
      "start": 7.98,
      "end": 8.58,
      "text": "The Fat Man."
    },
    {
      "start": 9.74,
      "end": 12.62,
      "text": "The telephone-bell was ringing when Spade returned to his office",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 12.8,
      "end": 16.18,
      "text": "sending Brigid O'Shaughnessy off to Effie Perine's house."
    },
    {
      "start": 16.8,
      "end": 17.94,
      "text": "He went to the telephone."
    },
    {
      "start": 18.64,
      "end": 18.92,
      "text": "\"Hello. . . .",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 19.48,
      "end": 19.94,
      "text": ". . . Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 20.74,
      "end": 21.26,
      "text": "this is Spade. . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.82,
      "end": 22.52,
      "text": ". . . Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 22.78,
      "end": 23.44,
      "text": "I got it."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.32,
      "end": 25.48,
      "text": "I've been waiting to hear from you. . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 25.92,
      "end": 26.44,
      "text": ". . . Who? . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 27.04,
      "end": 27.66,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 27.7,
      "end": 28.0,
      "text": "Gutman?"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.54,
      "end": 29.0,
      "text": "Oh, yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.18,
      "end": 29.408,
      "text": "sure! . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.0,
      "end": 30.1,
      "text": "Now—the sooner the better. . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.51,
      "end": 31.26,
      "text": "Twelve C. . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 34.56,
      "end": 35.14,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.64,
      "end": 36.22,
      "text": "Say fifteen minutes. . . ."
    },
    {
      "start": 36.5,
      "end": 36.98,
      "text": "Right.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 39.904,
      "end": 41.88,
      "text": "Spade sat on the corner of his desk beside",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 41.88,
      "end": 43.52,
      "text": "the telephone and rolled a cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.52,
      "end": 45.16,
      "text": "His mouth was"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.16,
      "end": 45.52,
      "text": "a hard"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.62,
      "end": 46.36,
      "text": "complacent v."
    },
    {
      "start": 46.58,
      "end": 47.52,
      "text": "His eyes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.66,
      "end": 49.32,
      "text": "watching his fingers make the cigarette,"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.6,
      "end": 50.86,
      "text": "smoldered over lower"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.0,
      "end": 52.28,
      "text": "lids drawn up straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.22,
      "end": 55.16,
      "text": "The door opened and Iva Archer came in.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 55.968,
      "end": 56.42,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 56.6,
      "end": 57.08,
      "text": "Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 57.22,
      "end": 57.42,
      "text": "honey,"
    },
    {
      "start": 57.8,
      "end": 61.66,
      "text": "in a voice as lightly amiable as his face had suddenly become."
    },
    {
      "start": 62.02,
      "end": 62.88,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 63.0,
      "end": 63.58,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 63.92,
      "end": 65.04,
      "text": "forgive me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.06,
      "end": 66.34,
      "text": "forgive me!"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.88,
      "end": 68.22,
      "text": "she cried in a choked voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 69.22,
      "end": 70.78,
      "text": "She stood just inside the door,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 71.36,
      "end": 74.18,
      "text": "wadding a black-bordered handkerchief in her small gloved hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.784,
      "end": 75.88,
      "text": "peering into his face"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.4,
      "end": 78.02,
      "text": "with frightened red and swollen eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 78.92,
      "end": 81.04,
      "text": "He did not get up from his seat on the desk-corner.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 81.4,
      "end": 82.22,
      "text": "He said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 82.38,
      "end": 82.98,
      "text": "\"Sure."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.14,
      "end": 84.12,
      "text": "That's all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 84.24,
      "end": 85.04,
      "text": "Forget it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 85.72,
      "end": 89.78,
      "text": "\"But, Sam,\" she wailed, \"I sent those policemen there",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 89.98,
      "end": 93.92,
      "text": "I was mad, crazy with jealousy, and I phoned them"
    },
    {
      "start": 94.4,
      "end": 96.2,
      "text": "that if they'd go there they'd learn something"
    },
    {
      "start": 96.18,
      "end": 97.38,
      "text": "about Miles's murder.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 98.24,
      "end": 99.7,
      "text": "\"What made you think that?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 100.32,
      "end": 103.90,
      "text": "\"Oh, I didn't! But I was mad, Sam, and I wanted to",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 103.92,
      "end": 104.42,
      "text": "hurt you.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 105.2,
      "end": 107.16,
      "text": "\"It made things damned awkward.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 107.44,
      "end": 109.94,
      "text": "He put his arm around her and drew her nearer."
    },
    {
      "start": 110.2,
      "end": 113.7,
      "text": "\"But it's all right now, only don't get any more crazy notions",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 113.98,
      "end": 114.42,
      "text": "like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 115.52,
      "end": 116.06,
      "text": "\"I won't,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 116.06,
      "end": 116.74,
      "text": "she promised,"
    },
    {
      "start": 116.96,
      "end": 117.56,
      "text": "\"ever."
    },
    {
      "start": 118.5,
      "end": 120.1,
      "text": "But you weren't nice to me last night."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.28,
      "end": 121.5,
      "text": "You were cold and"
    },
    {
      "start": 121.68,
      "end": 123.34,
      "text": "distant and wanted to get rid of me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 123.38,
      "end": 126.98,
      "text": "when I had come down there and waited so long to warn you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.06,
      "end": 127.66,
      "text": "and you?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 127.9,
      "end": 129.76,
      "text": "\"Warn me about what?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 130.92,
      "end": 131.5,
      "text": "\"About Phil.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 131.74,
      "end": 135.36,
      "text": "He's found out about—about you being in love with me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.48,
      "end": 138.26,
      "text": "and Miles had told him about my wanting a divorce,"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.94,
      "end": 140.5,
      "text": "though of course _he_ never knew what for,"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.56,
      "end": 144.12,
      "text": "and now Phil thinks we—you killed his brother"
    },
    {
      "start": 144.12,
      "end": 146.22,
      "text": "because he wouldn't give me the divorce so we"
    },
    {
      "start": 146.24,
      "end": 146.87,
      "text": "could get married."
    },
    {
      "start": 147.24,
      "end": 149.08,
      "text": "He told me he believed that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 149.16,
      "end": 151.14,
      "text": "and yesterday he went and told the police.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 152.32,
      "end": 152.72,
      "text": "\"That's nice,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 152.96,
      "end": 153.96,
      "text": "Spade said softly."
    },
    {
      "start": 154.12,
      "end": 158.38,
      "text": "\"And you came to warn me, and because I was busy you got up on your"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.38,
      "end": 159.52,
      "text": "ear and helped this damned Phil Archer stir things up.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 162.304,
      "end": 162.86,
      "text": "\"I'm sorry,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 163.04,
      "end": 163.7,
      "text": "she whimpered,"
    },
    {
      "start": 164.0,
      "end": 165.16,
      "text": "\"I know you won't"
    },
    {
      "start": 165.26,
      "end": 165.76,
      "text": "forgive me."
    },
    {
      "start": 163.98,
      "end": 167.68,
      "text": "I—I'm sorry,"
    },
    {
      "start": 167.8,
      "end": 168.28,
      "text": "sorry,"
    },
    {
      "start": 168.66,
      "end": 169.02,
      "text": "sorry.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 170.26,
      "end": 170.96,
      "text": "\"You ought to be,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 171.04,
      "end": 171.48,
      "text": "he agreed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 172.06,
      "end": 173.3,
      "text": "on your own account as well as"
    },
    {
      "start": 173.34,
      "end": 173.54,
      "text": "mine."
    },
    {
      "start": 173.78,
      "end": 176.78,
      "text": "Has Dundy been to see you since Phil did his talking?"
    },
    {
      "start": 176.96,
      "end": 178.56,
      "text": "Or anybody from the bureau?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 179.3,
      "end": 179.8,
      "text": "\"No.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 180.576,
      "end": 182.08,
      "text": "Alarm opened her eyes and mouth."
    },
    {
      "start": 183.04,
      "end": 183.42,
      "text": "\"They will,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 183.6,
      "end": 184.08,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 184.58,
      "end": 186.74,
      "text": "and it'd be just as well to not let them"
    },
    {
      "start": 186.74,
      "end": 187.46,
      "text": "find you here."
    },
    {
      "start": 188.16,
      "end": 190.14,
      "text": "Did you tell them who you were when you phoned?"
    },
    {
      "start": 191.02,
      "end": 191.66,
      "text": "\"Oh, no!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 191.98,
      "end": 193.5,
      "text": "I simply told them that if"
    },
    {
      "start": 193.62,
      "end": 195.22,
      "text": "they'd go to your apartment right away"
    },
    {
      "start": 195.32,
      "end": 197.72,
      "text": "they'd learn something about the murder and hung up.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 198.88,
      "end": 199.62,
      "text": "\"Where'd you phone from?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 199.9,
      "end": 202.56,
      "text": "\"The drug-store up above your place."
    },
    {
      "start": 202.84,
      "end": 203.36,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 203.42,
      "end": 203.82,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 204.0,
      "end": 204.38,
      "text": "dearest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 204.5,
      "end": 205.08,
      "text": "I—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 205.08,
      "end": 206.38,
      "text": "He patted her",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 206.5,
      "end": 207.68,
      "text": "shoulder and said pleasantly:"
    },
    {
      "start": 207.9,
      "end": 209.14,
      "text": "\"It was a dumb trick,"
    },
    {
      "start": 209.22,
      "end": 209.6,
      "text": "all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 210.02,
      "end": 210.84,
      "text": "but it's done now."
    },
    {
      "start": 211.78,
      "end": 212.32,
      "text": "You'd better run"
    },
    {
      "start": 212.4,
      "end": 214.68,
      "text": "along home and think up things to tell the police."
    },
    {
      "start": 215.42,
      "end": 216.36,
      "text": "You'll be hearing from them."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.056,
      "end": 218.12,
      "text": "Maybe it'd be best to"
    },
    {
      "start": 218.28,
      "end": 219.74,
      "text": "say 'no' right across the board.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 220.54,
      "end": 221.74,
      "text": "He frowned at something distant.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 221.98,
      "end": 223.7,
      "text": "\"Or maybe you'd better see"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.78,
      "end": 224.62,
      "text": "Sid Wise first."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.52,
      "end": 227.02,
      "text": "He removed his arm from around her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 227.16,
      "end": 228.88,
      "text": "took a card out of his pocket,"
    },
    {
      "start": 229.14,
      "end": 229.78,
      "text": "scribbled"
    },
    {
      "start": 229.78,
      "end": 231.0,
      "text": "three lines on its back,"
    },
    {
      "start": 231.12,
      "end": 231.9,
      "text": "and gave it to her."
    },
    {
      "start": 232.82,
      "end": 233.74,
      "text": "\"You can tell Sid everything.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 234.0,
      "end": 234.5,
      "text": "He frowned."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.62,
      "end": 235.32,
      "text": "\"Or almost"
    },
    {
      "start": 235.38,
      "end": 235.72,
      "text": "everything."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.34,
      "end": 238.46,
      "text": "Where were you the night Miles was shot?"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.8,
      "end": 239.74,
      "text": "\"Home,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 240.34,
      "end": 241.68,
      "text": "she replied without hesitating."
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}